Exaggerate: The claim exaggerates the increase in young voter turnout, stating it was "even higher than Obama's extraordinary victory in 2008" when in fact, there were fewer young voters this year compared to 2008.
Understate: The claim understates the actual numbers of young voters who participated in the Iowa caucus this year compared to 2008.
Lack enough support: The claim lacks enough support to back up the assertion that young voter turnout increased by 33%.
Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that an increase in the proportion of young voters indicates a significant increase in overall young voter turnout, which may not be the case.
Exist alternative explanation: The claim fails to consider alternative explanations for the increase in the proportion of young voters, such as changes in demographics or voter registration efforts.
